WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:02.910 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:00:02.910 --> 00:00:13.580 align:middle line:90%


00:00:13.580 --> 00:00:16.340 align:middle line:84%
>> So my name is
Doctor Sean Stephenson.

00:00:16.340 --> 00:00:20.900 align:middle line:84%
And when I was born, the
doctors in the delivery room

00:00:20.900 --> 00:00:24.530 align:middle line:84%
told my parents that I
wouldn't survive my first 24

00:00:24.530 --> 00:00:26.390 align:middle line:90%
hours of life.

00:00:26.390 --> 00:00:29.920 align:middle line:84%
And my inside joke is, now,
all those doctors are dead.

00:00:29.920 --> 00:00:33.440 align:middle line:84%
37 years later, I'm the
only doctor that remains.

00:00:33.440 --> 00:00:36.020 align:middle line:84%
And that goes over really
well everywhere but hospitals.

00:00:36.020 --> 00:00:41.450 align:middle line:84%
And I've lived an
incredible journey.

00:00:41.450 --> 00:00:47.150 align:middle line:84%
In this container, it's what
people first pay attention to.

00:00:47.150 --> 00:00:51.260 align:middle line:84%
But it's my goal that it
quickly disappears for them.

00:00:51.260 --> 00:00:55.610 align:middle line:84%
And I know I'm doing my job,
as a human, if I can get people

00:00:55.610 --> 00:01:02.720 align:middle line:84%
to see themselves in me and have
the wheelchair just evaporate.

00:01:02.720 --> 00:01:05.930 align:middle line:84%
So when people say, oh,
gosh, Sean, I don't even

00:01:05.930 --> 00:01:07.590 align:middle line:90%
see the wheelchair anymore.

00:01:07.590 --> 00:01:08.600 align:middle line:90%
I go, good.

00:01:08.600 --> 00:01:10.260 align:middle line:90%
I'm doing my job.

00:01:10.260 --> 00:01:13.940 align:middle line:84%
And I'm not ashamed of the way
I look or anything like that.

00:01:13.940 --> 00:01:18.290 align:middle line:84%
It's just I believe
that when you

00:01:18.290 --> 00:01:25.580 align:middle line:84%
have such identity around what
you can't do, you're miserable.

00:01:25.580 --> 00:01:30.760 align:middle line:84%
And my joke is a donut
doesn't go, I'm such a loser.

00:01:30.760 --> 00:01:32.350 align:middle line:90%
There's nothing in the center.

00:01:32.350 --> 00:01:33.770 align:middle line:90%
No, it's a donut.

00:01:33.770 --> 00:01:36.350 align:middle line:84%
There's not supposed to
be anything in the center.

00:01:36.350 --> 00:01:40.460 align:middle line:84%
And I'm a person
that doesn't consider

00:01:40.460 --> 00:01:46.680 align:middle line:84%
myself disabled, because
that's a term meaning not able.

00:01:46.680 --> 00:01:52.610 align:middle line:84%
And I've certainly lived a life
that has been more than able.

00:01:52.610 --> 00:01:55.670 align:middle line:84%
I think that this container has
been an interesting journey.

00:01:55.670 --> 00:01:58.460 align:middle line:84%
Because my whole
childhood, I was

00:01:58.460 --> 00:02:01.160 align:middle line:84%
riddled with physical
abuse, but not

00:02:01.160 --> 00:02:05.630 align:middle line:84%
by the hands of any other
human, but my genetics.

00:02:05.630 --> 00:02:07.610 align:middle line:90%
And I had loving--

00:02:07.610 --> 00:02:10.669 align:middle line:84%
still do-- parents,
an incredible sister,

00:02:10.669 --> 00:02:13.080 align:middle line:90%
and great neighbors, and family.

00:02:13.080 --> 00:02:16.100 align:middle line:84%
But my genetics
were quite abusive.

00:02:16.100 --> 00:02:22.890 align:middle line:84%
And I was put into
painful scenarios

00:02:22.890 --> 00:02:29.790 align:middle line:84%
nearly every few months of
my life, until I was 18.

00:02:29.790 --> 00:02:33.350 align:middle line:84%
Something as simple as
sneezing would break ribs.

00:02:33.350 --> 00:02:37.970 align:middle line:84%
Putting on a pair of pants too
quickly, I could snap a femur.

00:02:37.970 --> 00:02:41.790 align:middle line:84%
There are multiple times
that the physical pain

00:02:41.790 --> 00:02:48.000 align:middle line:84%
was nowhere near as abrasive
as the emotional trauma of what

00:02:48.000 --> 00:02:50.608 align:middle line:90%
it caused me to miss out on.

00:02:50.608 --> 00:02:52.650 align:middle line:84%
Vacations were planned,
and everything was ready.

00:02:52.650 --> 00:02:54.280 align:middle line:90%
And we were packed to go.

00:02:54.280 --> 00:02:58.680 align:middle line:84%
And as I was being wheeled
out the door by my parents,

00:02:58.680 --> 00:03:00.720 align:middle line:84%
I would cough too hard,
break a bunch of ribs,

00:03:00.720 --> 00:03:03.540 align:middle line:84%
and vacation was
canceled, because I needed

00:03:03.540 --> 00:03:05.710 align:middle line:90%
to stay at home, immobilized.

00:03:05.710 --> 00:03:12.480 align:middle line:84%
And so I feel like pain and
emotional upset from that pain

00:03:12.480 --> 00:03:15.630 align:middle line:90%
followed me my entire childhood.

00:03:15.630 --> 00:03:21.480 align:middle line:84%
And with that said, I
lived a glorious childhood.

00:03:21.480 --> 00:03:25.500 align:middle line:84%
And it all kind of
shifted in October,

00:03:25.500 --> 00:03:27.720 align:middle line:90%
when I was in fourth grade.

00:03:27.720 --> 00:03:30.630 align:middle line:84%
And there was a
special connection

00:03:30.630 --> 00:03:34.020 align:middle line:90%
that I had to Halloween.

00:03:34.020 --> 00:03:38.490 align:middle line:84%
Because in the US, when
you're a young boy or a girl,

00:03:38.490 --> 00:03:40.590 align:middle line:84%
and you're getting
ready for Halloween,

00:03:40.590 --> 00:03:42.057 align:middle line:90%
you're filled with excitement.

00:03:42.057 --> 00:03:44.140 align:middle line:84%
You want to show your
costume off to your friends.

00:03:44.140 --> 00:03:46.650 align:middle line:84%
You want to eat
way too much candy

00:03:46.650 --> 00:03:49.530 align:middle line:84%
and go on trick
or treating dates

00:03:49.530 --> 00:03:51.550 align:middle line:90%
with your friends and all this.

00:03:51.550 --> 00:03:56.730 align:middle line:84%
And then one morning, on
Halloween, I was in my costume.

00:03:56.730 --> 00:04:00.000 align:middle line:84%
And I'm out of my wheelchair,
and I'm on the floor.

00:04:00.000 --> 00:04:02.040 align:middle line:90%
And my mom's in the kitchen.

00:04:02.040 --> 00:04:05.310 align:middle line:84%
She's making my the lunches
and taking the backpacks

00:04:05.310 --> 00:04:06.550 align:middle line:90%
out to the car.

00:04:06.550 --> 00:04:10.020 align:middle line:84%
And I'm rolling around, and
I'm like, oh, I look so good.

00:04:10.020 --> 00:04:13.260 align:middle line:84%
And I can't wait to show this
costume off to my friends.

00:04:13.260 --> 00:04:15.600 align:middle line:84%
And as I'm rolling around,
I catch my left leg

00:04:15.600 --> 00:04:17.130 align:middle line:90%
on the corner of the door.

00:04:17.130 --> 00:04:20.584 align:middle line:84%
And I bent it back, and I
snapped it at the femur.

00:04:20.584 --> 00:04:21.959 align:middle line:84%
And if you've ever
broken a bone,

00:04:21.959 --> 00:04:24.240 align:middle line:84%
you know there's a
bit of a time delay

00:04:24.240 --> 00:04:28.860 align:middle line:84%
between hearing the sound of
the snap and feeling the pain.

00:04:28.860 --> 00:04:31.500 align:middle line:84%
And even though it's a
fraction of a second,

00:04:31.500 --> 00:04:33.540 align:middle line:90%
it feels like an eternity.

00:04:33.540 --> 00:04:37.230 align:middle line:84%
Because you visualize everything
you're going to miss out on.

00:04:37.230 --> 00:04:42.840 align:middle line:84%
You visualize all the nights
of excruciating twitches

00:04:42.840 --> 00:04:45.600 align:middle line:84%
that will wake you up
screaming and blood curdling

00:04:45.600 --> 00:04:48.350 align:middle line:84%
screams, because it feels
like you're being stabbed.

00:04:48.350 --> 00:04:51.340 align:middle line:84%
And all that comes
rushing into your brain

00:04:51.340 --> 00:04:55.230 align:middle line:84%
when you've been exposed
to that amount of pain.

00:04:55.230 --> 00:04:57.120 align:middle line:84%
So my mom, she comes
running in the room,

00:04:57.120 --> 00:04:59.470 align:middle line:90%
because I started screaming.

00:04:59.470 --> 00:05:03.450 align:middle line:84%
And I was screaming both in
pain and in emotional agony.

00:05:03.450 --> 00:05:07.710 align:middle line:84%
Because I thought, why do
I have to go through this?

00:05:07.710 --> 00:05:09.330 align:middle line:84%
What did I ever do
to deserve this?

00:05:09.330 --> 00:05:11.640 align:middle line:90%
I was one of the good kids.

00:05:11.640 --> 00:05:13.290 align:middle line:90%
I did my homework.

00:05:13.290 --> 00:05:15.480 align:middle line:90%
I was nice to my neighbors.

00:05:15.480 --> 00:05:17.130 align:middle line:90%
I was polite.

00:05:17.130 --> 00:05:22.710 align:middle line:84%
Why was I being
punished for being me?

00:05:22.710 --> 00:05:25.770 align:middle line:90%
And I was furious.

00:05:25.770 --> 00:05:29.400 align:middle line:84%
And my mom, she would normally
play this game with me

00:05:29.400 --> 00:05:32.940 align:middle line:84%
when I would break a bone to
try to transport my mind as far

00:05:32.940 --> 00:05:35.250 align:middle line:90%
away from the pain as possible.

00:05:35.250 --> 00:05:38.760 align:middle line:84%
She would say, sweetie,
what was your favorite part

00:05:38.760 --> 00:05:42.090 align:middle line:90%
about our last vacation?

00:05:42.090 --> 00:05:45.810 align:middle line:84%
Except that day, I didn't
want to play any games.

00:05:45.810 --> 00:05:48.660 align:middle line:90%
I was furious.

00:05:48.660 --> 00:05:51.740 align:middle line:90%
I didn't think it was fair.

00:05:51.740 --> 00:05:54.860 align:middle line:84%
And she could see
that anger in my eyes.

00:05:54.860 --> 00:06:00.800 align:middle line:84%
So my mom leaned back,
and she formulated,

00:06:00.800 --> 00:06:05.830 align:middle line:84%
I believe, a question that has
really set me up for everything

00:06:05.830 --> 00:06:08.530 align:middle line:90%
wonderful in my life.

00:06:08.530 --> 00:06:13.480 align:middle line:84%
It's why I do what I do
now and have ever since.

00:06:13.480 --> 00:06:19.360 align:middle line:84%
She looked in my eyes,
and she said, sweetie,

00:06:19.360 --> 00:06:25.968 align:middle line:84%
is this going to be a gift
or a burden in your life?

00:06:25.968 --> 00:06:28.697 align:middle line:84%
First of all, I
thought she was crazy.

00:06:28.697 --> 00:06:30.030 align:middle line:90%
You and I have had gifts, right?

00:06:30.030 --> 00:06:32.380 align:middle line:84%
They come on our birthday,
and we open them up

00:06:32.380 --> 00:06:35.850 align:middle line:90%
with joy and excitement.

00:06:35.850 --> 00:06:42.420 align:middle line:84%
But what happened next, I tell
my scientific, skeptic friends

00:06:42.420 --> 00:06:47.010 align:middle line:84%
I can't explain what
happened physically.

00:06:47.010 --> 00:06:49.350 align:middle line:84%
But it's what I
experienced emotionally.

00:06:49.350 --> 00:06:54.870 align:middle line:84%
It was like this warm wind
of wisdom filled the room,

00:06:54.870 --> 00:06:59.660 align:middle line:84%
and circled around my
body, and just calmed me.

00:06:59.660 --> 00:07:03.770 align:middle line:84%
And in fourth grade, such a
young, impressionable age,

00:07:03.770 --> 00:07:05.170 align:middle line:90%
I got clarity on my life.

00:07:05.170 --> 00:07:07.690 align:middle line:90%


00:07:07.690 --> 00:07:12.660 align:middle line:84%
I realized that I loved my
life amidst all that pain.

00:07:12.660 --> 00:07:16.950 align:middle line:84%
And maybe there was a
bigger, grander purpose

00:07:16.950 --> 00:07:20.530 align:middle line:90%
to why I was in this container.

00:07:20.530 --> 00:07:23.910 align:middle line:84%
Maybe the reason was to teach
the rest of the human race

00:07:23.910 --> 00:07:27.556 align:middle line:84%
how to love their lives
amidst their pain.

00:07:27.556 --> 00:07:30.120 align:middle line:90%
And it sent me on a journey.

00:07:30.120 --> 00:07:32.910 align:middle line:84%
And knowing the
purpose to your pain

00:07:32.910 --> 00:07:35.700 align:middle line:84%
doesn't make the
pain go away, but it

00:07:35.700 --> 00:07:40.800 align:middle line:84%
gives you fuel to keep pushing
forward and not want to quit,

00:07:40.800 --> 00:07:44.310 align:middle line:84%
not want to check out,
not want to numb yourself.

00:07:44.310 --> 00:07:49.860 align:middle line:84%
Stay in it, be mindful, and
look for the gifts in your life,

00:07:49.860 --> 00:07:56.730 align:middle line:84%
because we all have control
over what we make things mean.

00:07:56.730 --> 00:08:00.210 align:middle line:84%
Our interpretations are
our greatest freedom.

00:08:00.210 --> 00:08:02.160 align:middle line:90%
You can lock me in a prison.

00:08:02.160 --> 00:08:04.440 align:middle line:84%
You could break every
bone in my body,

00:08:04.440 --> 00:08:08.430 align:middle line:84%
but you can't take my ability
to choose what I make something

00:08:08.430 --> 00:08:10.720 align:middle line:90%
mean away from me.

00:08:10.720 --> 00:08:12.720 align:middle line:84%
And that's what
sets me free from,

00:08:12.720 --> 00:08:15.240 align:middle line:84%
unfortunately, the rest of the
human race, who I feel like

00:08:15.240 --> 00:08:17.580 align:middle line:90%
is in prison, mentally.

00:08:17.580 --> 00:08:21.900 align:middle line:84%
Because they think things are
being done to them, instead of

00:08:21.900 --> 00:08:23.760 align:middle line:90%
with and for them.

00:08:23.760 --> 00:08:28.700 align:middle line:84%
And in that young age of fourth
grade, I looked at my mom.

00:08:28.700 --> 00:08:33.150 align:middle line:90%
I said, I think I get it.

00:08:33.150 --> 00:08:35.070 align:middle line:90%
And that propelled me forward.

00:08:35.070 --> 00:08:37.230 align:middle line:84%
It's not that I never had
a bad day beyond that.

00:08:37.230 --> 00:08:38.280 align:middle line:90%
I certainly did.

00:08:38.280 --> 00:08:41.520 align:middle line:84%
I had multiple fractures
beyond that point, surgeries--

00:08:41.520 --> 00:08:43.860 align:middle line:84%
I was laughed at
when I would leave

00:08:43.860 --> 00:08:47.720 align:middle line:84%
my house by kids and people
that had never seen somebody

00:08:47.720 --> 00:08:49.550 align:middle line:90%
that looked like me.

00:08:49.550 --> 00:08:52.070 align:middle line:84%
I definitely went through
moments of being ostracized.

00:08:52.070 --> 00:08:54.330 align:middle line:90%
And it didn't make it easier.

00:08:54.330 --> 00:08:58.170 align:middle line:84%
It just made me
not want to quit.

00:08:58.170 --> 00:09:01.610 align:middle line:90%
And that's what I do now.

00:09:01.610 --> 00:09:04.590 align:middle line:84%
As a world thought
leader, I'm on this planet

00:09:04.590 --> 00:09:09.600 align:middle line:84%
to look human beings in the eye
and say, I know it's painful.

00:09:09.600 --> 00:09:12.650 align:middle line:84%
I wish it didn't
have to be painful.

00:09:12.650 --> 00:09:14.370 align:middle line:90%
You have a choice.

00:09:14.370 --> 00:09:17.640 align:middle line:84%
Are you going to see it
as a gift or a burden?

00:09:17.640 --> 00:09:20.660 align:middle line:84%
And when you hold that
space for a human being who

00:09:20.660 --> 00:09:24.660 align:middle line:84%
is floundering in pain,
and suffering, and agony--

00:09:24.660 --> 00:09:26.550 align:middle line:84%
you just hold,
lovingly, that space

00:09:26.550 --> 00:09:30.900 align:middle line:84%
for them, a certain percentage
of them will wake up.

00:09:30.900 --> 00:09:32.810 align:middle line:90%
Not everybody.

00:09:32.810 --> 00:09:35.640 align:middle line:84%
I personally believe
that, in this lifetime,

00:09:35.640 --> 00:09:38.100 align:middle line:84%
it's not for
everybody to get it.

00:09:38.100 --> 00:09:39.530 align:middle line:90%
I wish it was.

00:09:39.530 --> 00:09:42.960 align:middle line:84%
But there will be
some who won't get it.

00:09:42.960 --> 00:09:47.530 align:middle line:84%
And I live by a
Coast Guard motto.

00:09:47.530 --> 00:09:48.780 align:middle line:90%
The motto of the Coast Guard--

00:09:48.780 --> 00:09:52.290 align:middle line:84%
I don't know if it's true, but
I have heard it a few times.

00:09:52.290 --> 00:09:56.180 align:middle line:84%
And I love it-- it says,
when the Coast Guard comes

00:09:56.180 --> 00:09:59.520 align:middle line:84%
upon a shipwreck, and they
only have so much room

00:09:59.520 --> 00:10:02.610 align:middle line:84%
in the helicopter to save
the people that are drowning,

00:10:02.610 --> 00:10:03.790 align:middle line:90%
you know who they save?

00:10:03.790 --> 00:10:07.470 align:middle line:90%


00:10:07.470 --> 00:10:08.830 align:middle line:90%
The ones that swim towards them.

00:10:08.830 --> 00:10:12.860 align:middle line:90%


00:10:12.860 --> 00:10:16.850 align:middle line:84%
And not everybody
swims toward us.

00:10:16.850 --> 00:10:18.730 align:middle line:84%
A victim runs into
a burning building

00:10:18.730 --> 00:10:22.060 align:middle line:90%
screaming help me, help me.

00:10:22.060 --> 00:10:26.500 align:middle line:84%
And I've been doing
this for 22 years

00:10:26.500 --> 00:10:30.310 align:middle line:84%
as a professional speaker, 10
years as an online personality,

00:10:30.310 --> 00:10:35.770 align:middle line:84%
16 years as a therapist, and
it still gets me, emotionally.

00:10:35.770 --> 00:10:42.630 align:middle line:84%
Because there are those that,
no matter how hard I try,

00:10:42.630 --> 00:10:44.400 align:middle line:90%
they'll never get it.

00:10:44.400 --> 00:10:46.340 align:middle line:90%
Because they don't want it.

00:10:46.340 --> 00:10:48.420 align:middle line:84%
And when you spend
all your energy trying

00:10:48.420 --> 00:10:51.910 align:middle line:84%
to save those that
won't swim toward you,

00:10:51.910 --> 00:10:53.790 align:middle line:90%
you miss all of those that do.

00:10:53.790 --> 00:10:56.790 align:middle line:90%
