00:11:01.290 --> 00:11:03.770 align:middle line:90%
So I saw a Ted Talk, once.

00:11:03.770 --> 00:11:05.840 align:middle line:84%
I wish I could remember
the name of the speaker,

00:11:05.840 --> 00:11:08.280 align:middle line:84%
because I'd love
to give him credit.

00:11:08.280 --> 00:11:10.230 align:middle line:90%
But he said it best.

00:11:10.230 --> 00:11:16.450 align:middle line:84%
He said, what determines
the gravity of a planet?

00:11:16.450 --> 00:11:19.230 align:middle line:90%
It's the size of the planet.

00:11:19.230 --> 00:11:23.030 align:middle line:84%
And what human
beings do is, when

00:11:23.030 --> 00:11:24.890 align:middle line:84%
they start taking
on more obligations,

00:11:24.890 --> 00:11:30.770 align:middle line:84%
and responsibilities, and power,
and influence, and success,

00:11:30.770 --> 00:11:33.110 align:middle line:90%
their planet grows.

00:11:33.110 --> 00:11:35.960 align:middle line:84%
When the planet grows,
they get more gravity.

00:11:35.960 --> 00:11:37.985 align:middle line:84%
When they get more gravity,
it's harder to move.

00:11:37.985 --> 00:11:39.095 align:middle line:90%
It takes more muscle.

00:11:39.095 --> 00:11:44.720 align:middle line:84%
It takes more effort to do
what you used to do with ease.

00:11:44.720 --> 00:11:46.970 align:middle line:84%
And so what most
people do is, instead

00:11:46.970 --> 00:11:50.070 align:middle line:84%
of strengthening themselves
and saying I got this.

00:11:50.070 --> 00:11:51.290 align:middle line:90%
I'm going to keep going.

00:11:51.290 --> 00:11:55.740 align:middle line:84%
They go, what if I could
shrink my planet back down?

00:11:55.740 --> 00:11:57.740 align:middle line:84%
And so that's when
they self sabotage,

00:11:57.740 --> 00:11:59.260 align:middle line:90%
because they screw it up.

00:11:59.260 --> 00:12:02.730 align:middle line:84%
They get into that fight with
that person that they love,

00:12:02.730 --> 00:12:06.020 align:middle line:84%
or they cheat, or they screw
up that business thing.

00:12:06.020 --> 00:12:08.430 align:middle line:84%
It's all, oftentimes,
unconscious.

00:12:08.430 --> 00:12:10.940 align:middle line:84%
So the gravity is
decreased, because they

00:12:10.940 --> 00:12:13.190 align:middle line:90%
shrunk their planet.

00:12:13.190 --> 00:12:17.760 align:middle line:84%
And I've seen this in my own
life with my own choices.

00:12:17.760 --> 00:12:20.540 align:middle line:84%
There'll be times when
I'm like, gosh, why am I

00:12:20.540 --> 00:12:22.190 align:middle line:90%
screwing this up, continually?

00:12:22.190 --> 00:12:25.760 align:middle line:84%
And then I do the reflection
or I do the journaling,

00:12:25.760 --> 00:12:29.650 align:middle line:84%
and I realize, oh, because
the gravity was scary.

00:12:29.650 --> 00:12:33.380 align:middle line:84%
And I was more comfortable
with the certainty

00:12:33.380 --> 00:12:37.840 align:middle line:84%
of the smaller sized planet
than the larger planet.

00:12:37.840 --> 00:12:40.610 align:middle line:84%
And I've shrunk my planet,
and I've expanded my planet

00:12:40.610 --> 00:12:42.830 align:middle line:90%
multiple times in my life.

00:12:42.830 --> 00:12:46.070 align:middle line:84%
And I'm learning
to pay attention

00:12:46.070 --> 00:12:51.890 align:middle line:84%
to what I'm doing here
in my day to day choices.

00:12:51.890 --> 00:12:56.510 align:middle line:90%
And I am a slow learner.

00:12:56.510 --> 00:13:01.400 align:middle line:84%
People say, how many times do
you have to learn something?

00:13:01.400 --> 00:13:04.310 align:middle line:90%
And I go, until it sticks.

00:13:04.310 --> 00:13:07.640 align:middle line:84%
And one of my other
mentors, Evan Pagan,

00:13:07.640 --> 00:13:13.720 align:middle line:84%
said, when does a person
truly learn something?

00:13:13.720 --> 00:13:16.070 align:middle line:84%
The answer is when they've
changed their behavior.

00:13:16.070 --> 00:13:20.090 align:middle line:84%
Until a behavior is changed,
you haven't learned anything.

00:13:20.090 --> 00:13:21.710 align:middle line:90%
You can know to eat right.

00:13:21.710 --> 00:13:22.940 align:middle line:90%
You can know to exercise.

00:13:22.940 --> 00:13:24.650 align:middle line:90%
You can know to save money.

00:13:24.650 --> 00:13:28.850 align:middle line:84%
You can know to be kind to
people and be a good listener.

00:13:28.850 --> 00:13:31.830 align:middle line:84%
But until you actually
start doing those things,

00:13:31.830 --> 00:13:34.970 align:middle line:90%
you really haven't learned them.

00:13:34.970 --> 00:13:41.660 align:middle line:84%
And so I'm a man,
as I mature, and I'm

00:13:41.660 --> 00:13:44.840 align:middle line:84%
hoping that I'm maturing,
depending on the day.

00:13:44.840 --> 00:13:46.950 align:middle line:84%
Or if you ask my wife,
it may not be true.

00:13:46.950 --> 00:13:50.570 align:middle line:84%
But as I mature on
this planet, I'm

00:13:50.570 --> 00:13:55.070 align:middle line:84%
seeing that everyone
is a reflection of me.

00:13:55.070 --> 00:13:58.250 align:middle line:84%
And if there's somebody
or something outside of me

00:13:58.250 --> 00:14:01.810 align:middle line:84%
that I hate, that means I
got some more work to do.

00:14:01.810 --> 00:14:04.060 align:middle line:84%
It doesn't mean I have to
agree with every human being

00:14:04.060 --> 00:14:07.590 align:middle line:84%
or appreciate all human
beings' behaviors.

00:14:07.590 --> 00:14:09.360 align:middle line:90%
I don't.

00:14:09.360 --> 00:14:13.030 align:middle line:84%
But the moment I start
having hatred, or disdain,

00:14:13.030 --> 00:14:18.350 align:middle line:84%
or irritation, it's time to
go back to work on myself.

00:14:18.350 --> 00:14:20.610 align:middle line:84%
When people see me,
they think, oh, I

00:14:20.610 --> 00:14:23.785 align:middle line:84%
would love to have the peace,
and confidence, and happiness

00:14:23.785 --> 00:14:25.540 align:middle line:90%
of Sean Stephenson.

00:14:25.540 --> 00:14:28.390 align:middle line:84%
And that's just flattering
to hear to my ego.

00:14:28.390 --> 00:14:31.780 align:middle line:84%
But the truth of
the matter is they

00:14:31.780 --> 00:14:35.650 align:middle line:84%
don't see the work that
goes into being me.

00:14:35.650 --> 00:14:37.660 align:middle line:84%
And if I could just
brag for a second

00:14:37.660 --> 00:14:44.140 align:middle line:84%
about behind the scenes of
me, I have a consistent set

00:14:44.140 --> 00:14:48.430 align:middle line:84%
of rituals that I have to
enact, or my insecurities

00:14:48.430 --> 00:14:50.590 align:middle line:90%
eat me alive.

00:14:50.590 --> 00:14:52.130 align:middle line:90%
People don't know this about me.

00:14:52.130 --> 00:14:54.550 align:middle line:84%
But if you got to
know me closely,

00:14:54.550 --> 00:14:59.000 align:middle line:84%
you would see in my home
office and in my phone,

00:14:59.000 --> 00:15:02.710 align:middle line:90%
I have a series of 16 rituals.

00:15:02.710 --> 00:15:06.130 align:middle line:84%
And if I don't do four
of those rituals a day,

00:15:06.130 --> 00:15:08.350 align:middle line:84%
my insecurities
will eat me alive.

00:15:08.350 --> 00:15:09.520 align:middle line:90%
I'll doubt myself.

00:15:09.520 --> 00:15:12.320 align:middle line:90%
I will question my capability.

00:15:12.320 --> 00:15:16.810 align:middle line:84%
But if I do these self care
rituals, you and no army

00:15:16.810 --> 00:15:18.790 align:middle line:90%
can make me feel bad.

00:15:18.790 --> 00:15:24.760 align:middle line:84%
And these rituals are so simple,
because I found the insecurity.

00:15:24.760 --> 00:15:31.300 align:middle line:84%
It's one of the greatest
thieves of a human's value.

00:15:31.300 --> 00:15:37.560 align:middle line:84%
And a couple of years ago,
maybe about seven years ago,

00:15:37.560 --> 00:15:39.310 align:middle line:90%
one of my mentors sat me down.

00:15:39.310 --> 00:15:42.030 align:middle line:90%
And he said, why were you born?

00:15:42.030 --> 00:15:44.560 align:middle line:90%


00:15:44.560 --> 00:15:46.010 align:middle line:84%
He just kept asking
over and over.

00:15:46.010 --> 00:15:48.093 align:middle line:90%
Why were you born?

00:15:48.093 --> 00:15:50.010 align:middle line:84%
And I kept giving him
superficial answers just

00:15:50.010 --> 00:15:50.940 align:middle line:90%
to shut him up.

00:15:50.940 --> 00:15:52.020 align:middle line:90%
And he was like, no.

00:15:52.020 --> 00:15:53.250 align:middle line:90%
Why were you born?

00:15:53.250 --> 00:15:56.270 align:middle line:84%
And then finally,
I just got calm.

00:15:56.270 --> 00:15:59.520 align:middle line:90%
And I got clear.

00:15:59.520 --> 00:16:03.480 align:middle line:84%
I was born to rid the
world of insecurity.

00:16:03.480 --> 00:16:06.880 align:middle line:84%
He said he felt the hairs on
the back of his neck stand up.

00:16:06.880 --> 00:16:07.680 align:middle line:90%
And he said, yes.

00:16:07.680 --> 00:16:09.060 align:middle line:90%
You were.

00:16:09.060 --> 00:16:11.808 align:middle line:84%
Because if there is
anybody on this planet that

00:16:11.808 --> 00:16:14.350 align:middle line:84%
could convince the human race
they don't need to be insecure,

00:16:14.350 --> 00:16:16.770 align:middle line:90%
it's you.

00:16:16.770 --> 00:16:23.010 align:middle line:84%
And I believe the insecurities
are those moments when we

00:16:23.010 --> 00:16:24.890 align:middle line:90%
don't feel like we're enough--

00:16:24.890 --> 00:16:28.530 align:middle line:84%
not tall enough, smart enough,
rich enough, pretty enough,

00:16:28.530 --> 00:16:30.860 align:middle line:84%
handsome enough,
confident enough.

00:16:30.860 --> 00:16:35.100 align:middle line:84%
We feel like we're
lacking something.

00:16:35.100 --> 00:16:40.080 align:middle line:84%
And that feeling of
lack is dangerous,

00:16:40.080 --> 00:16:41.760 align:middle line:84%
because we'll go
out and do things

00:16:41.760 --> 00:16:44.250 align:middle line:84%
to try to prove that we're
enough that are often very

00:16:44.250 --> 00:16:48.120 align:middle line:84%
destructive and, eventually,
potentially addictive.

00:16:48.120 --> 00:16:53.550 align:middle line:84%
And as a human being that's here
to rid the world of insecurity,

00:16:53.550 --> 00:16:56.940 align:middle line:84%
I've done a lot of work
on looking into my own.

00:16:56.940 --> 00:17:01.320 align:middle line:84%
So I am the laboratory
for the human race.

00:17:01.320 --> 00:17:05.140 align:middle line:84%
I'm like, why am I
feeling this insecure?

00:17:05.140 --> 00:17:07.980 align:middle line:84%
And I'll go deep
inside, and I'll reverse

00:17:07.980 --> 00:17:09.900 align:middle line:90%
engineer what took place.

00:17:09.900 --> 00:17:11.230 align:middle line:90%
What did I just think about?

00:17:11.230 --> 00:17:13.020 align:middle line:90%
Where was I focused?

00:17:13.020 --> 00:17:16.440 align:middle line:84%
And I will reverse engineer
what caused the insecurity,

00:17:16.440 --> 00:17:17.760 align:middle line:90%
and how can I turn it around.

00:17:17.760 --> 00:17:21.040 align:middle line:84%
And I got two massive
insights about Insecurity

00:17:21.040 --> 00:17:23.220 align:middle line:90%
for the human race.

00:17:23.220 --> 00:17:27.930 align:middle line:84%
One is the cure that I'm
happy to share with you.

00:17:27.930 --> 00:17:32.670 align:middle line:84%
And the other insight that
I had is even more crazy.

00:17:32.670 --> 00:17:35.970 align:middle line:84%
And that is to cure
insecurity, you

00:17:35.970 --> 00:17:37.830 align:middle line:84%
have to realize it's
never going away.

00:17:37.830 --> 00:17:40.540 align:middle line:90%


00:17:40.540 --> 00:17:42.690 align:middle line:84%
And once you realize
it's never going away,

00:17:42.690 --> 00:17:46.390 align:middle line:84%
