So when you get
mean comments, you

00:52:18.350 --> 00:52:20.420 align:middle line:84%
know you got some
more work to do.

00:52:20.420 --> 00:52:24.350 align:middle line:84%
It's a deep thought
that scares us.

00:52:24.350 --> 00:52:26.680 align:middle line:90%
So I have to two tattoos.

00:52:26.680 --> 00:52:28.760 align:middle line:84%
One of them, I share
with my wife, Mindy.

00:52:28.760 --> 00:52:31.130 align:middle line:84%
And it's that our love
for each other is infinite

00:52:31.130 --> 00:52:34.850 align:middle line:84%
and that we are so much greater
than our roles and titles.

00:52:34.850 --> 00:52:37.400 align:middle line:84%
And the other one is
C is greater than E.

00:52:37.400 --> 00:52:41.120 align:middle line:84%
And that means cause
is greater than effect.

00:52:41.120 --> 00:52:44.840 align:middle line:84%
Everything that happens,
I am a cause for,

00:52:44.840 --> 00:52:47.180 align:middle line:90%
because I got out of bed today.

00:52:47.180 --> 00:52:50.750 align:middle line:84%
And when something
happens, like this year,

00:52:50.750 --> 00:52:52.650 align:middle line:84%
I smashed into the
back of a semi truck

00:52:52.650 --> 00:52:54.710 align:middle line:90%
going 75 miles an hour.

00:52:54.710 --> 00:52:55.890 align:middle line:90%
I almost died.

00:52:55.890 --> 00:53:00.710 align:middle line:84%
And I was a cause for getting
in the vehicle that day.

00:53:00.710 --> 00:53:04.930 align:middle line:84%
And had my life come to an
end, it wasn't, oh, it's so sad

00:53:04.930 --> 00:53:06.520 align:middle line:90%
that Sean ran into that truck.

00:53:06.520 --> 00:53:09.980 align:middle line:84%
No, Sean got in
the car that day.

00:53:09.980 --> 00:53:12.482 align:middle line:84%
No matter what
happens to you, you

00:53:12.482 --> 00:53:13.940 align:middle line:84%
have to take
ownership for the fact

00:53:13.940 --> 00:53:16.640 align:middle line:84%
that you got out
of bed that day.

00:53:16.640 --> 00:53:19.250 align:middle line:84%
And when you live at
cause, you own the results

00:53:19.250 --> 00:53:20.450 align:middle line:90%
that are happening to you.

00:53:20.450 --> 00:53:23.900 align:middle line:84%
The biggest, whiny,
victim mentality lives

00:53:23.900 --> 00:53:26.690 align:middle line:90%
at effect, which is, why me?

00:53:26.690 --> 00:53:28.700 align:middle line:84%
What did I ever do
to deserve this?

00:53:28.700 --> 00:53:36.280 align:middle line:84%
And that mentality of it's not
my fault. It's somebody else,

00:53:36.280 --> 00:53:40.070 align:middle line:84%
and I have to blame so
I can be free of this.

00:53:40.070 --> 00:53:41.180 align:middle line:90%
But they're never free.

00:53:41.180 --> 00:53:44.750 align:middle line:84%
When you are blaming
anything outside of yourself,

00:53:44.750 --> 00:53:46.100 align:middle line:90%
you're never free.

00:53:46.100 --> 00:53:49.720 align:middle line:84%
You are a victim to
the external world.

00:53:49.720 --> 00:53:51.920 align:middle line:84%
And I just choose
not to be that.

00:53:51.920 --> 00:53:58.607 align:middle line:84%
Some things don't make
sense in the moment.

00:53:58.607 --> 00:54:00.440 align:middle line:84%
But I believe, over the
course of our lives,

00:54:00.440 --> 00:54:04.330 align:middle line:90%
we can see the greater picture.

00:54:04.330 --> 00:54:07.670 align:middle line:84%
And whenever something is
unfair or upsetting to me,

00:54:07.670 --> 00:54:11.470 align:middle line:84%
I just know, wait,
I'm too zoomed in.

00:54:11.470 --> 00:54:12.780 align:middle line:90%
I zoom out.

00:54:12.780 --> 00:54:18.141 align:middle line:84%
I'm going to see that this is
not happening to me but for me.

00:54:18.141 --> 00:54:21.640 align:middle line:84%
And if I'm wrong, I'd
rather live in that reality.

00:54:21.640 --> 00:54:26.950 align:middle line:84%
Because the opposite is
those realistic cynics

00:54:26.950 --> 00:54:30.790 align:middle line:90%
that are never happy.

00:54:30.790 --> 00:54:33.340 align:middle line:84%
I'm OK with people
being skeptics.

00:54:33.340 --> 00:54:35.530 align:middle line:84%
Skeptic means you
look into things.

00:54:35.530 --> 00:54:37.200 align:middle line:84%
You want to make
sure that it's valid.

00:54:37.200 --> 00:54:38.000 align:middle line:90%
Great.

00:54:38.000 --> 00:54:39.400 align:middle line:90%
Be skeptical.

00:54:39.400 --> 00:54:42.938 align:middle line:84%
Cynics look for how
it's not possible.

